{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6930f93a-f276-4f96-9b9a-d9a1b1b97a1b","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework Support Dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL; MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported (EOL; MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. **Update target frameworks** — replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later) and `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0` (or later).\n\n2. **Consolidate packages** — MSTest v3 ships a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\n3. **Review breaking API changes** — some attributes and asserts were renamed or removed in v3.\n\nWould you like me to perform the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3937429a-bd08-4417-a2e6-32b319ff3ed3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has specific framework requirements. Let me analyze the compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package or `MSTest.TestFramework` 3.x) dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ or .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `net5.0` is no longer supported (it's out of support and MSTest v3 dropped it)\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is also no longer supported by MSTest v3\n\n\n- `net462` should still work fine\n\nSo the user will hit compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`. Also worth noting that MSTest v3 consolidated everything into a single `MSTest` package, so they won't need separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages anymore.","outputTokens":490,"requestId":"B81F:3862EE:E02810:EE1E18:6A044DD1"},"id":"cd2887a5-0d79-47d4-95ff-f3bd93908158","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:10:24.297Z","parentId":"e13901fe-50fe-4bca-9c51-ed490e6d10fb"}
